@node "Installing TurboText"

TurboText must be installed in your system before you can use it. The
package comes with an easy to use installation utility that can configure
the software for operation on a floppy-only system, or on a system
equipped with a hard disk.

	@{" Floppy Disk Installation      " link "Floppy Disk Installation"}
	@{" Hard Disk Installation        " link "Hard Disk Installation"}
	@{" Upgrading From TurboText 1.03 " link "Upgrading From TurboText 1.03"}

@endnode


@node "Floppy Disk Installation"

To install TurboText on a floppy-only system, you need a blank floppy
disk, which will be formatted for use by TurboText. To prepare the floppy
disk for use, you must run the TurboText installation utility.

@{fg highlight}To run the TurboText installation utility:@{fg text}

	1 - Insert the TurboText_1 disk in any floppy drive.

	2 - Open the TurboText_1 disk icon by double-clicking on it with
	    the left mouse button.

	3 - Double-click the left mouse button on the installation
	    icon that is in the language of your choice.

	4 - Follow the on-screen directions that are then presented.

Once started, the Installation utility will install everything that is
needed to run TurboText.

@endnode


@node "Hard Disk Installation"

To install TurboText on a system equipped with a hard disk, you must run
the TurboText installation utility.

@{fg highlight}To run the TurboText installation utility:@{fg text}

	1 - Insert the TurboText2.0 disk in any floppy drive.

	2 - Open the TurboText2.0 disk icon by double-clicking on it with
	    the left mouse button.

	3 - Double-click the left mouse button on the installation
	    icon that is in the language of your choice.

	4 - Follow the on-screen directions that are then presented.

Once started, the installation utility will install everything that is
needed to run TurboText. If you had a previous version of TurboText
installed, all the needed files will be automatically upgraded to
TurboText 2.0.

During installation, the utility will ask you questions about how you would
like TurboText setup. You must answer these questions in order for the
installation to complete successfully. At any time during the installation
process, you can click on the @{b}Help@{ub} button to obtain context-sensitive help
about what's about to happen during installation.

@endnode


@node "Upgrading From TurboText 1.03"

To upgrade from a previous version of TurboText, you simply have to run
the standard installation procedure.

@endnode







