@{u}Standard Hot Key Sequences@{uu}

  @{b}[Ctrl]-[Alt]-A@{ub}  Activate the last document window used
  @{b}[Ctrl]-[Alt]-O@{ub}  Open a new document window and bring up the file requester
  @{b}[Ctrl]-[Alt]-S@{ub}  Bring the editor screen to the front of all screens
  @{b}[Ctrl]-[Alt]-U@{ub}  Request the editor unload itself from memory
  @{b}[Ctrl]-[Alt]-W@{ub}  Open a new document window


@{u}Standard Mouse Sequences@{uu}

  Holding down the left button and pushing the mouse off the bottom or top
  edges of the window scrolls the display. While the left button is still
  down, clicking the right button brings the cursor back to its original
  cursor position and stops scrolling.

  Double-clicking the left button marks the start of a selection block.

  Double-clicking the middle button marks the start of a vertical selection
  block.

  Holding down the left button and clicking the middle button creates a
  fold.

  Holding down the middle button and clicking the right button toggles the
  fold under the cursor from shown to hidden and back.

** Note that the middle mouse button is not available on the standard Amiga
   mouse


