@node "Center"

Format:		Center

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Horizontally center the current line or selected block.

Specifications: 
Center centers the current line or currently @{" selected block " link "Selection Blocks"}. The
centering is done relative to column one in the document, and the current
@{" right margin " link "Preferences - Editing"}.

If there is currently a selected block, the operation is applied to this
block, otherwise the operation is applied to the current line only.

If this command is invoked while a @{" vertical block " link "Vertical Selection Blocks"} is selected, it
functions exactly like when a normal block is selected and centers all the
lines within the block.

The centering is done by first removing extra spaces on both ends of every
line, then by adding the necessary number of spaces to the left of the
line to center the line between column one and the right margin. If a line
is longer than the right margin, it is not affected.

See Also: @{" Justify         " link "Justify"}
