	  @{" ShiftRight      " link "ShiftRight"}

	  @{" Extras/Center " link "The Extras Menu"}

@endnode


@node "CenterView"

Format:		CenterView [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]

Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Vertically center the cursor within the current view.

Specifications: 
CenterView scrolls the contents of the @{" current view " link "Multi-View Editing"} in order to position
the cursor as close as possible to the middle of the view. The actual
position of the cursor within the document is not changed, only its
location on the screen. Note that the centering only occurs the next time
the display is redrawn.

Specifying no option, or the ON option, both cause centering to occur the
next time the display is redrawn. To force the display to be updated, you
can use the @{" UpdateView " link "UpdateView"} command.

Certain commands such as @{" MoveBookmark " link "MoveBookmark"} or @{" Find " link "Find"} automatically request
centering of the cursor once they complete. To defeat this automatic
centering, the OFF option can be specified. The TOGGLE option toggles
whether centering is to occur.

See Also: @{" GetViewInfo " link "GetViewInfo"}
