@node "Conv2Spaces"

Format:		Conv2Spaces [tab width] [SOL]

Template:	WIDTH/N,SOL/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Convert the tab characters of the current document or selected block to
equivalent spaces.

Specifications: 
Conv2Spaces converts all tab characters from the current document or
@{" selected block " link "Selection Blocks"} to an equivalent number of spaces, preserving the same
screen formatting. The replacement process takes into account the currently
defined @{" tab width " link "Preferences - Tabs"}. The optional WIDTH parameter overrides the current
tab width value. Replacing tabs with spaces may be useful for certain
printers or computer systems that do not handle tabs correctly.

If there is currently a selected block, the operation is applied to this
block, otherwise the operation is applied to the entire document.

Starting with TurboText 2.0, the SOL option lets you limit the space
conversion process to the beginning of lines only. As soon as a character
which is neither a space or a tab is encountered, the conversion is
stopped for that line.

This command does not alter tab characters contained in quoted strings.

See Also: @{" Conv2Tabs " link "Conv2Tabs"}

	  @{" Extras/Convert Tabs To Spaces " link "The Extras Menu"}

