@node "EncryptBlk"

Format:		EncryptBlk

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Encode the currently selected block using caesarian encryption.

Specifications: 
EncryptBlk applies the caesarian encryption algorithm to the currently
@{" selected block " link "Selection Blocks"}. Caesarian encryption, often referred to as rot13, is a
simple technique which exchanges the letters A-M with the letters N-Z. This
has the effect of making the text unreadable. Applying the encryption a
second time reverts the text to its original form.

Caesarian encryption is used on some electronic networks to post messages
that are not meant to be read by accident. These messages require a
specific action to be read - the application of the encryption method to
them.

