@endnode


@node "GetPriority"

Format:		GetPriority

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Return the current task priority of the editor.

Specifications: 
GetPriority returns the task priority associated with the editor.
Priorities can range from -128 to 127, 0 being normal. The information is
returned in the @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} RESULT variable, and consists of a single number
representing the task priority.

This command can only be used through the ARexx interface.

See Also: @{" SetPriority " link "SetPriority"}

@endnode


@node "GetReadOnly"

Format:		GetReadOnly

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Return the current setting of the read-only option.

Specifications: 
GetReadOnly returns whether the current document is in @{" read-only mode " link "Read-Only Mode"}.
If a document is in read-only mode, it cannot be modified. The information
is returned in the @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} RESULT variable, and consists of either ON or
OFF, depending if the document is in read-only mode or not.

This command can only be used through the ARexx interface.

See Also: @{" SetReadOnly " link "SetReadOnly"}

@endnode


@node "GetScreenInfo"

Format:		GetScreenInfo

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Return information about the screen the current document window is opened
on.

Specifications: 
GetScreenInfo returns the position, size, and depth of the screen the
current document window is opened on.

The information is returned in the @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} RESULT variable, and consists
of the screen's position, its size, the number of bit-planes it contains,
its X and Y clips, and its @{" public screen name " link "Public Screens"}. The format of the
returned value is @{b}left top width height depth xclip yclip name@{ub}. For
example, @{b}0 0 640 200 2 320 120 "Workbench"@{ub} indicates the screen is at
position 0,0 is 640 pixels wide and 200 pixels high, with 2 bit-planes, has
an X clip of 320 and a Y clip of 120, and has a public name of "Workbench".

The X and Y clips represent the amount of the screen that is actually
visible on the display. These values will differ from the width and height
when operating on a virtual screen. That is, these values tell you how
much of the screen can be seen at once. In such a case, the left and top
values indicate how much the screen has scrolled.

This command can only be used through the ARexx interface.

See Also: @{" GetWindowInfo " link "GetWindowInfo"}

@endnode


@node "GetVersion"

Format:		GetVersion

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Return version information about the editor.

Specifications: 
GetVersion returns the name, version number, and date associated with the
editor currently running.

The information is returned in the @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} RESULT variable, and consists of
the editor name, the version number and the date this version of the editor
was generated. For example: @{b}TurboText 2.0 (21.7.94)@{ub}.

This command can only be used through the ARexx interface.

@endnode


@node "GetViewInfo"

Format:		GetViewInfo

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Return information about the current view.

Specifications: 
GetViewInfo returns the number of the current @{" view " link "Multi-View Editing"}, the number of lines
of text which can fit within this view, the number of columns of characters
that can fit, the line number of the first line visible in the view, and
the column number of the first character visible to the left of the view.

The information is returned in the @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} RESULT variable, and consists
of five numbers indicating respectively the view number, the number of
lines which can fit in the view, the number of characters that can fit, the
top line displayed in the view, and the number of the leftmost column of
text in the view. The format of the returned value is @{b}view lines chars
topline leftchar@{ub} such as @{b}0 23 77 12 1@{ub} to indicate that view 0 is the
current view, 23 lines of text can fit in it, 77 characters per line can
fit in the view, line 12 is at the top of the view, and column 1 is the
first column of text visible on the left edge. Note that there are
currently two possible views, 0 and 1.

This command can only be used through the ARexx interface.

See Also: @{" CenterView  " link "CenterView"}
	  @{" ScrollView  " link "ScrollView"}
	  @{" SizeView    " link "SizeView"}
	  @{" SplitView   " link "SplitView"}
	  @{" SwapViews   " link "SwapViews"}
	  @{" SwitchView  " link "SwitchView"}
	  @{" UpdateView  " link "UpdateView"}

@endnode


@node "GetWindowInfo"

Format:		GetWindowInfo

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Return information about the current document window.

Specifications: 
GetWindowInfo returns whether the current @{" document window " link "The TurboText Document Window"} is iconified,
and its current position and size, the minimum window dimensions, and the
number of @{" views " link "Multi-View Editing"} within the window.

The information is returned in the @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} RESULT variable, and consists
of an on/off value indicating whether the window is iconified, followed by
four numbers indicating respectively the x and y coordinates of the window
(in pixels) as well as its width and height (also in pixels), followed by
two numbers indicating the minimum width and height of the window, finally
followed by another number indicating the number of views visible in the
window.

The format of the returned value is @{b}icon x y width height minwidth
minheight numviews@{ub}. For example, @{b}OFF 0 10 640 190 100 30 1@{ub} indicates the
window is not iconified, is at coordinates 0,10, is 640 pixels wide and 190
pixels tall, can be made as small as 100 pixels wide and 30 pixels high,
and there is currently a single view visible in the window. The coordinates
are relative to the top left of the current screen.

This command can only be used through the ARexx interface.

See Also: @{" GetScreenInfo  " link "GetScreenInfo"}
	  @{" IconifyWindow  " link "IconifyWindow"}
	  @{" MoveSizeWindow " link "MoveSizeWindow"}
	  @{" MoveWindow     " link "MoveWindow"}
	  @{" SizeWindow     " link "SizeWindow"}

@endnode


@node "GetWord"

Format:		GetWord

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Return the word currently under the cursor.

Specifications: 
GetWord returns the word currently under the cursor to an ARexx macro. The
word is returned in the @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} RESULT variable. If the cursor is not
currently on a word, the previous word is returned.

This command can only be used through the ARexx interface.

See Also: @{" CompleteTemplate " link "CompleteTemplate"}
