@node "Justify"

Format:		Justify

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Horizontally full-justify the current line or selected block.

Specifications: 
Justify full-justifies the current line or currently @{" selected block " link "Selection Blocks"}. The
justification is done relative to column one in the document, and the
current @{" right margin " link "Preferences - Editing"}.

If there is currently a selected block, the operation is applied to this
block, otherwise the operation is applied to the current line only.

If this command is invoked while a @{" vertical block " link "Vertical Selection Blocks"} is selected, it
functions exactly like when a normal block is selected and justifies all
the lines within the block.

The justification is done by first removing extra spaces on both ends of
every line, then by adding the necessary number of spaces between
individual words in order to justify the line. If a line is longer than
the right margin, it is not affected.

See Also: @{" Center          " link "Center"}
