@node "MarkBlk"

Format:		MarkBlk [VERTICAL] [TOGGLEVERTICAL]

Template:	VERTICAL/S,TOGGLEVERTICAL/S,WORD/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Mark the current cursor position as the start of a selection block.

Specifications: 
MarkBlk marks the current cursor position as the start of the
@{" selection block " link "Selection Blocks"}. If a block is already selected, MarkBlk has the effect
of cancelling the selected block, unless the TOGGLEVERTICAL option is used.

When invoked without parameters, this command starts a normal selection
block. The VERTICAL option can be provided, which starts a
@{" vertical selection block " link "Vertical Selection Blocks"} instead. The TOGGLEVERTICAL option has the
effect of toggling the selected block between normal and vertical mode.
This can be handy when bound to a mouse button.

Starting with TurboText 2.0, the WORD option can be provided which has the
effect of selecting the word currently under the cursor.

