@node "MoveAutomark"

Format:		MoveAutomark

Template:	,

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Move the cursor to the position indicated by the automatic bookmark.

Specifications: 
MoveAutomark moves the cursor to the position indicated by the
@{" automatic bookmark " link "The Automatic Bookmark"}. The automatic bookmark is set automatically by
TurboText to the current cursor position prior to performing operations
likely to move the cursor by a significant amount within the document. This
lets you return instantly to the original cursor position prior to the
operation.

MoveAutomark affects the automatic bookmark itself. When executing this
command, the cursor is moved to the position indicated by the automatic
bookmark, and the cursor position before the movement becomes the
automatic bookmark position. Thus using this command, you can easily
toggle the cursor position between two locations within the document by
executing this command every time you wish to switch position.

The commands that set the automatic bookmark are:

	@{" Find           " link "Find"}
	@{" FindChange     " link "FindChange"}
	@{" Move           " link "Move"}
	@{" MoveBookmark   " link "MoveBookmark"}
	@{" MoveDownScr    " link "MoveDownScr"}
	@{" MoveEOF        " link "MoveEOF"}
	@{" MoveLastChange " link "MoveLastChange"}
	@{" MoveSOF        " link "MoveSOF"}
	@{" MoveUpScr      " link "MoveUpScr"}
	@{" PasteClip      " link "PasteClip"}

In addition to these commands, scrolling through the document using the
mouse sets the automatic bookmark to the cursor position before scrolling
started.

See Also: @{" ClearBookmark " link "ClearBookmark"}
	  @{" MoveBookmark  " link "MoveBookmark"}
	  @{" SetBookmark   " link "SetBookmark"}

	  @{" Search/Go To Auto-Bookmark " link "The Search Menu"}

@endnode


