@node "OpenDoc"

Format:		OpenDoc [FILEREQ] [WAIT] [MACRO <macro name>]
			[WINDOW <window description>]
			[PUBSCREEN <public screen name>]
			[SETTINGS <prefs file name>]
			[DEFINITIONS <definition file name>]
			[filename]

Template:	FILEREQ/S,WAIT/S,MACRO/K,WINDOW/K,PUBSCREEN/K,SETTINGS/K,
		DEFINITIONS/K,NAME/F

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Create a new document.

Specifications: 
OpenDoc opens a @{" document window " link "The TurboText Document Window"} ready to edit a new document.

The FILEREQ option can be provided to cause the new document window to open
a @{" file requester " link "The File Requester"}, where a file to load can be selected. The NAME
parameter can also be provided in which case the new document loads the
given file from disk automatically.

OpenDoc normally returns to you right after the document window is
created. The WAIT option lets you wait until the document created is
closed before returning.

The MACRO parameter lets you specify the name of an @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} macro to
execute as soon as the document window has been opened, and any requested
document has been loaded.

The WINDOW parameter lets you specify the type and dimension of the
document window created for the new document. The format for the
description string is:

    <left/top/width/height/iconified left/iconified top/ICONIFIED/CLOSED>

where:

  left/top/width/height indicate the initial position and size of the
  document window that will be created.

  iconified left/iconified top indicate the initial position of the
  iconified version of the document window.

  ICONIFIED indicates that the document window should be initially opened
  in the iconified state. The window can then be de-iconified by using
  the @{" IconifyWindow " link "IconifyWindow"} command.

  CLOSED indicates that the document should be loaded, but no document
  window should be opened for it. The document window can be opened at a
  later time using the @{" ControlWindow " link "ControlWindow"} command.

All of the parameters to the WINDOW keyword are optional. The current
default value is used for any missing parameter. For example:

	WINDOW=//200/300

means to use the current default left and top values, and to force a size
of 200x300.

Opening a document without a window by using the /CLOSED option of the
WINDOW parameter can be very useful. You can use TurboText as a sort of
editing engine, driven entirely through ARexx.

The PUBSCREEN parameter lets you specify the name of the public screen
TurboText should open the document window on.

The SETTINGS parameter lets you specify the name of a TurboText
preferences file to load and use for the new document.

The DEFINITIONS parameter lets you specify the name of a TurboText
@{" definition file " link "Definition Files"} to load and use for the new document.

When invoked through ARexx, the ARexx port name associated with the new
document window is returned in the ARexx RESULT variable.

See Also: @{" CloseDoc " link "CloseDoc"}

	  @{" Project/Open New... " link "The Project Menu"}
	  @{" Windows/New         " link "The Windows Menu"}

@endnode


@node "OpenFile"

