@node "RequestBool"

Format:		RequestBool <requester title> <prompt string>

Template:	TITLE/A,PROMPT/A

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Get a yes/no response from the user.

Specifications: 
RequestBool opens a small window with two gadgets labelled @{b}OK@{ub} amd @{b}Cancel@{ub}.
The TITLE parameter specifies the title of the window. The PROMPT parameter
specifies the lines of text to display as a question to the user.

The resulting value is returned in the @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} RESULT variable and
consists of YES if the user selected the positive choice and NO if he
selected the negative choice.

Note that starting with TurboText 2.0, the @{" RequestChoice " link "RequestChoice"} command
provides a more flexible replacement for the RequestBool command.

This command can only be used through the ARexx interface.

See Also: @{" RequestChoice " link "RequestChoice"}
