	  @{" RequestNum    " link "RequestNum"}
	  @{" RequestStr    " link "RequestStr"}

@endnode


@node "RequestChoice"

Format:		RequestChoice <requester title> <prompt string> <gadgets>

Template:	TITLE/A,PROMPT/A,GADGETS/A

Release:	Version 2.0

Purpose: 
Get a choice out a list of options from the user.

Specifications: 
RequestChoice opens a small window with a series of gadgets at the bottom,
and lets the user pick one of these gadgets. The TITLE parameter specifies
the title of the window. The PROMPT parameter specifies the lines of text
to display as a question to the user. Multiple lines in the prompt can be
specified using the *n escape sequence to indicate line breaks.

The GADGETS parameter specifies the gadgets to be displayed at the bottom
of the requester. The gadgets are listed in left to right order, separated
with a vertical bar (|). For example, supplying "OK|Maybe|Cancel" would
result in a requester with three gadgets labelled "OK", "Maybe" and
"Cancel".

The resulting value is returned in the @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} RESULT variable and
consists of 0 if the user picked the rightmost gadget, 1 for the leftmost
gadget, 2 for the second gadget from the left, 3 for the next one, etc. For
example, a requester with 4 gadgets would have the following return values
associated with each gadget selection:

   OK  Maybe  Sometimes  Cancel
   1   2      3          0

An example use of this command is:

  RequestChoice "A Title" "A two line *n prompt string" "one|two|three"

The above line will create a requester called "A Title", containing a two
line question, and three gadgets at the bottom.

This command can only be used through the ARexx interface.

See Also: @{" RequestBool " link "RequestBool"}
	  @{" RequestFile " link "RequestFile"}
	  @{" RequestNum  " link "RequestNum"}
	  @{" RequestStr  " link "RequestStr"}

@endnode


@node "RequestFile"

Format:		RequestFile [SAVEMODE] [DRAWERSONLY] [PROMPT <prompt>]
			    [PATTERN <pattern>] [path]

Template:	SAVEMODE/S,DRAWERSONLY/SPROMPT/K,PATTERN/K,PATH/F

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Get a filename from the user using the file requester.

Specifications: 
RequestFile opens the @{" file requester " link "The File Requester"} and prompts the user to select a
file. The PROMPT parameter allows you to specify the text which appears in
the title bar of the file requester. The PATTERN parameter specifies the
pattern string to include in the file requester's @{b}Pattern@{ub} gadget. The PATH
parameter specifies the directory path to include in the file requester's
@{b}Drawer@{ub} gadget.

Starting with TurboText 2.0, the SAVEMODE option is available, and causes
a save-mode file requester to be opened. This option should be used
whenever the file requester is being used to get the filename for a new
file being created.

Starting with TurboText 2.0, the DRAWERSONLY option is available, and
causes the file requester displayed to only show drawers, and allow the
selection of drawers. This is useful when you want to ask the user for a
directory where to put files, or get files from.

The resulting filename is returned in the @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} RESULT variable. If the
user cancels the file requester, an error is generated.

This command can only be used through the ARexx interface.

See Also: @{" RequestBool   " link "RequestBool"}
	  @{" RequestChoice " link "RequestChoice"}
	  @{" RequestNum    " link "RequestNum"}
	  @{" RequestStr    " link "RequestStr"}

@endnode


