@node "SaveClip"

Format:		SaveClip [QUIET] [NOBACKUP] [NOICON] [APPEND] [filename]

Template:	QUIET/S,NOBACKUP/S,NOICON/S,APPEND/S,NAME/F

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Save the current contents of the clipboard to disk.

Specifications: 
SaveClip saves the current contents of the @{" clipboard " link "Using The Clipboard"} to a file on disk.

If the @{b}Load And Save Project Icons@{ub} option in the @{" Icons " link "Preferences - Icons"} section of the
preferences requester is currently on, this command also saves an icon
along with the clip. If the destination file already has an icon on disk,
no new icon is created. The NOICON option can be provided to prevent an
icon from ever being saved.

If the @{b}Create Backups When Saving@{ub} option in the @{" Backup Creation " link "Preferences - Backup Creation"} section
of the preferences requester is currently on, a backup is created if there
is already a file with the same name on disk. The NOBACKUP option can be
specified to prevent a backup from ever being created.

An optional filename may be specified. If the filename is present, the
editor attempts to save the contents of the clipboard in that file. If the
filename is not present, then the @{" file requester " link "The File Requester"} is opened, allowing the
user to select a file. Note that when a filename is specified, it must be
fully qualified (i.e. have a complete directory path).

Starting with TurboText 2.0, the QUIET option prevents TurboText from
bringing up any confirmation requesters during the save operation.

Starting with TurboText 2.0, the APPEND option lets you specify that the
data being saved should be appended to the destination file, if the file
already exists.

When saving to an existing file, the protection bits of the file are
preserved, except for the @{b}A@{ub} (Archive) bit which is cleared.

See Also: @{" OpenClip  " link "OpenClip"}
	  @{" PasteClip " link "PasteClip"}
