@node "ScrollView"

Format:		ScrollView <screen line> [RELATIVE]

Template:	LINE/N/A,RELATIVE/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Scroll the current view to position the cursor on a specific line.

Specifications: 
ScrollView scrolls the contents of the current @{" view " link "Multi-View Editing"} in order to position
the cursor on a specific screen line. The single required parameter
specifies the screen line the cursor should be moved to. The actual
position of the cursor within the document is not changed, only its
location on the screen.

When the RELATIVE option is specified, the line number provided is
interpreted as relative to the current view position instead of being an
absolute line number. So for example, @{b}ScrollView 1 Relative@{ub} causes the
display to scroll by one line instead of scrolling to line 1.

See Also: @{" CenterView  " link "CenterView"}
