@endnode


@node "SetARexxCache"

Format:		SetARexxCache

Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 2.0

Purpose: 
Control whether the ARexx macro cache is on.

Specifications: 
SetARexxCache lets you control whether the editor's @{" ARexx macro cache " link "The ARexx Macro Cache"} is
enabled. Provided with the ON option this command turns the cache on. This
causes the editor to keep macros in memory when they are first used.
Following uses of the macro can use the version in memory instead of having
to reload The OFF option turns the cache off, while the TOGGLE option
toggles the current setting.

See Also: @{" FlushARexxCache " link "FlushARexxCache"}
	  @{" GetARexxCache   " link "GetARexxCache"}

@endnode


@node "SetBackground"

Format:		SetBackground

Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change the background mode of the editor.

Specifications: 
SetBackground lets you control the @{" background mode " link "Startup Options"} of the editor.
Provided with the ON option this command turns on background mode. This
forces the editor to stay in memory even though all document windows might
be closed. The OFF option turns background mode off, while the TOGGLE
option toggles the current setting.

See Also: @{" GetBackground " link "GetBackground"}

@endnode


@node "SetBookmark"

Format:		SetBookmark <bookmark number>

Template:	BOOKMARK/N/A

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Install a bookmark at the current cursor position.

Specifications: 
SetBookmark registers a @{" bookmark " link "Bookmarks"} at the current cursor location. That
bookmark can then later be used to quickly jump to the current location.
The single parameter specifies the number that should be assigned to the
bookmark, use this number in a subsequent @{" MoveBookmark " link "MoveBookmark"} command. Bookmark
0 is reserved as a place holder for @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} macros.

See Also: @{" ClearBookmark " link "ClearBookmark"}
	  @{" MoveAutomark  " link "MoveAutomark"}
	  @{" MoveBookmark  " link "MoveBookmark"}

@endnode


@node "SetChar"

Format:		SetChar <character>

Template:	CHAR/A

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change the character currently under the cursor.

Specifications: 
SetChar changes the character currently under the cursor. The parameter
specifies the character that should replace the current character.

See Also: @{" GetChar        " link "GetChar"}
	  @{" Insert         " link "Insert"}
	  @{" SwapChars      " link "SwapChars"}
	  @{" Text           " link "Text"}
	  @{" ToggleCharCase " link "ToggleCharCase"}

@endnode


@node "SetCurrentDir"

Format:		SetCurrentDir <directory name>

Template:	NAME/F

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change the document's current directory.

Specifications: 
SetCurrentDir lets you change the current directory associated with the
current document. Every document has a distinct current directory
associated with it, just like every process on the Amiga has its own
current directory. The single parameter specifies the name of the new
current directory.

See Also: @{" GetCurrentDir " link "GetCurrentDir"}
	  @{" GetFileInfo   " link "GetFileInfo"}
	  @{" GetFilePath   " link "GetFilePath"}
	  @{" SetFilePath   " link "SetFilePath"}

@endnode


@node "SetCursor"

Format:		SetCursor [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]

Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 2.0

Purpose: 
Change whether the text cursor should be displayed.

Specifications: 
SetCursor changes whether the text cursor is displayed in the document
window. The ON option displays the cursor, OFF prevents it from being
displayed, and TOGGLE changes to the opposite of what the current setting
is.

See Also: @{" GetCursor " link "GetCursor"}

@endnode


@node "SetDisplayLock"

Format:		SetDisplayLock [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]

Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change the display lock state of the current document.

Specifications: 
SetDisplayLock changes the current setting of the display lock. When a
document's display is locked, it is not updated when changes are made to
it. This is useful when executing an @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} macro which does a lot of
editing. The editing can be done quickly without updating the display for
every command, and unlocked once done. The display is then updated if
needed.

The @{" UpdateView " link "UpdateView"} command can be used when the display is locked in order
to force a screen update.

The ON option locks the document's display, the OFF option unlocks the
display and allows it to be updated, and the TOGGLE option changes to the
opposite of the current setting.

The @{b}UnsetLocks@{ub} @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} macro is a convenient way to unlock all locks set
in TurboText. This can be useful when developing and testing ARexx macros.

See Also: @{" GetLockInfo  " link "GetLockInfo"}
	  @{" SetInputLock " link "SetInputLock"}

@endnode


@node "SetFilePath"

Format:		SetFilePath <new path>

Template:	NAME/F

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change the file path and name of the current document.

Specifications: 
SetFilePath alters the current file path and name of a loaded document.
This command changes the title of the document window, and affects the name
used in any future @{" SaveFile " link "SaveFile"} operation.

See Also: @{" GetCurrentDir " link "GetCurrentDir"}
	  @{" GetFileInfo   " link "GetFileInfo"}
	  @{" GetFilePath   " link "GetFilePath"}
	  @{" SetCurrentDir " link "SetCurrentDir"}

@endnode


@node "SetInputLock"

Format:		SetInputLock [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]

Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change the state of the document's input lock.

Specifications: 
SetInputLock changes the current setting of the input lock. When a
document's input is locked, it is not possible to manipulate the document's
menus or enter keyboard sequences. This is useful when executing an
@{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} macro to prevent the user from interfering with the execution of
the macro.

The ON option locks the document's input, the OFF option unlocks it, and
the TOGGLE option changes to the opposite of the current setting.

The @{b}UnsetLocks@{ub} @{" ARexx " link "TurboText And ARexx"} macro is a convenient way to unlock all locks set
in TurboText. This can be useful when developing and testing ARexx macros.

See Also: @{" GetLockInfo    " link "GetLockInfo"}
	  @{" SetDisplayLock " link "SetDisplayLock"}

@endnode


@node "SetMeta"

Format:		SetMeta [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]

Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Sets the special META qualifier for the next character typed in.

Specifications: 
SetMeta exists to facilitate emulations of other text editors. Many editors
such as EMACS or VI require multiple key sequences to execute a command.
For example, to save a file in EMACS, @{b}[Ctrl]-X@{ub} must be entered, followed by
@{b}[Ctrl]-S@{ub}.

SetMeta causes the special META qualifier to be set the next time a
character is typed in. This would be used in keyboard mappings such as:

	CTRL-X       SetMeta
	META-CTRL-S  SaveFile

This means that when @{b}[Ctrl]-X@{ub} is entered, this causes the next key sequence
to have the META qualifier set. When @{b}[Ctrl]-S@{ub} is then entered, the
@{" SaveFile " link "SaveFile"} command is executed.

Specifying the OFF option cancels the META qualifier, and the TOGGLE
option inverts the current setting.

See Also: @{" SetMeta2 " link "SetMeta2"}
	  @{" SetMode  " link "SetMode"}
	  @{" SetMode2 " link "SetMode2"}

@endnode


@node "SetMeta2"

Format:		SetMeta2 [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]

Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Sets the special META2 qualifier for the next character typed in.

Specifications: 
SetMeta2 exists to facilitate emulations of other text editors. Many
editors such as EMACS or VI require multiple key sequences to execute a
command. For example, to save a file in EMACS, @{b}[Ctrl]-X@{ub} must be entered,
followed by @{b}[Ctrl]-S@{ub}.

SetMeta2 causes the special META2 qualifier to be set the next time a
character is typed in. This would be used in keyboard mappings such as:

	CTRL-X        SetMeta2
	META2-CTRL-S  SaveFile

This means that when @{b}[Ctrl]-X@{ub} is entered, this causes the next key sequence
to have the META2 qualifier set. When @{b}[Ctrl]-S@{ub} is then entered, the
@{" SaveFile " link "SaveFile"} command is executed.

Specifying the OFF option cancels the META qualifier, and the TOGGLE
option inverts the current setting.

See Also: @{" SetMeta  " link "SetMeta"}
	  @{" SetMode  " link "SetMode"}
	  @{" SetMode2 " link "SetMode2"}

@endnode


@node "SetMode"

Format:		SetMode [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]

Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change the state of the special MODE qualifier for future keyboard
sequences.

Specifications: 
SetMode exists to facilitate emulations of other text editors. Many
editors such as EMACS or VI operate in various modes, such as command mode
or text insertion mode.

SetMode causes the special MODE qualifier to be set every time a character
sequence is entered. This would be used in keyboard mappings such as:

	ESC          SetMode ON
	MODE-CTRL-S  SaveFile

This means that when @{b}[Esc]@{ub} is entered, this causes following key sequences
to have the MODE qualifier set. When @{b}[Ctrl]-S@{ub} is then entered, the
@{" SaveFile " link "SaveFile"} command is executed.

The ON option causes future keyboard sequences to have the MODE qualifier
set, the OFF option cancels this, and the TOGGLE option switches to the
opposite of the current setting.

See Also: @{" SetMeta  " link "SetMeta"}
	  @{" SetMeta2 " link "SetMeta2"}
	  @{" SetMode2 " link "SetMode2"}

@endnode


