Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change the state of the special MODE2 qualifier for future keyboard
sequences.

Specifications: 
SetMode2 exists to facilitate emulations of other text editors. Many
editors such as EMACS or VI operate in various modes, such as command mode
or text insertion mode.

SetMode2 causes the special MODE2 qualifier to be set every time a
character sequence is entered. This would be used in keyboard mappings
such as:

	ESC           SetMode2 ON
	MODE2-CTRL-S  SaveFile

This means that when @{b}[Esc]@{ub} is entered, this causes following key sequences
to have the MODE2 qualifier set. When @{b}[Ctrl]-S@{ub} is then entered, the
@{" SaveFile " link "SaveFile"} command is executed.

The ON option causes future keyboard sequences to have the MODE2 qualifier
set, the OFF option cancels this, and the TOGGLE option switches to the
opposite of the current setting.

