			TextColor <pen number> |
			TranslateCRs  [ON | OFF | TOGGLE] |
			WordWrap [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]
			ZoomGadget [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]   ]

Template:	PREFS/A,SETTING/F

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change preferences settings.

Specifications: 
SetPrefs lets you change the value of any preferences setting. The first
parameter specifies which setting to affect. The second parameter
indicates the new value for this setting.

The value for AutoSaveDelay is given in minutes. The value for RightMargin
is given in number of characters from the left edge of the document. The
values associated with ScreenSize are given in screen pixels.

Whenever changing display-related options, you must call the
@{" RemakeScreen " link "RemakeScreen"} command for these changes to take effect. This is true for
the following options:

    BufferedWindow, FontName, FontSize, ScreenMode,
    ScreenName, ScreenSize, ScrollGadget, ZoomGadget

A ScrollGadget value of 0 puts the scroll gadget on the right of the
document window, a value of 1 puts it on the left, and a value of 2 means
no scroll gadget at all.

A SaveEOLAs value of 0 causes TurboText to mark the end of lines in files
it creates with the character LF. A value of 1 uses a CR character
instead. A value of 2 uses both CR and LF characters. Finally, a value of
3 will cause TurboText to use the same end-of-line characters as were
found when the current document was loaded in. If the document was not
loaded in, and was instead just created, it will be saved with LF only.

The conversion type parameter for ConversionOnLoad, ConversionOnPrint, and
ConversionOnSave can be 0 for none, 1 for tabs to spaces, and 2 for spaces
to tabs.

The value for FoldIndent can be a positive number, which indicates the
exact amount of fold spacing. If the value supplied is -1, it tells
TurboText to do dynamic fold spacing, based on the folds in the current
document.

