@node "SetPriority"

Format:		SetPriority <priority>

Template:	PRIORITY/N/A

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change the task priority of the editor.

Specifications: 
SetPriority lets you change the task priority associated with the editor.
Priorities can range from -128 to 127, 0 being normal. The single required
parameter specifies the new priority for the editor's task.

 @{fg highlight} »»»  @{fg text}Increasing the priority of a task tends to give it more CPU time in
 @{fg highlight} »»»  @{fg text}a busy system, this can increase responsiveness of the program.
 @{fg highlight} »»»  @{fg text}Increasing the priority too high can block other important system
 @{fg highlight} »»»  @{fg text}functions and can crash the system. Priorities should be kept in the
 @{fg highlight} »»»  @{fg text}range -4 to 4 unless special circumstances exist.

See Also: @{" GetPriority " link "GetPriority"}

@endnode


@node "SetQuoteMode"

Format:	        SetQuoteMode [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]

Template:       ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 1.03

Purpose: 
Control the quote mode of the editor.

Specifications: 
Entering keyboard sequences that are mapped to TurboText commands causes
the commands to be executed instead of the keyboard sequences to be
interpreted as characters. For example, if @{b}[Ctrl]-O@{ub} toggles Overstrike
mode, then it is not possible to actually enter @{b}[Ctrl]-O@{ub} within the
document.

SetQuoteMode causes the next keyboard sequence entered to be taken as is,
and to not be interpreted as a command. Once the next keyboard sequence is
entered, quote mode is automatically disabled again.

@endnode


@node "SetReadOnly"

Format:		SetReadOnly [ON | OFF | TOGGLE]

Template:	ON/S,OFF/S,TOGGLE/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Change the read-only mode of the current document.

Specifications: 
SetReadOnly changes the @{" read-only mode " link "Read-Only Mode"} of the document. The ON option
sets the document to read-only, the OFF option sets the document to normal
mode, and the TOGGLE option changes the mode to the opposite of what it is
currently at.

See Also: @{" GetReadOnly " link "GetReadOnly"}

	  @{" Project/Read-Only " link "The Project Menu"}

@endnode


@node "SetStatusBar"

Format:		SetStatusBar [TEMPORARY] <status bar text>

Template:	TEMPORARY/S,TEXT/F

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Set the text displayed in the editor's status area.

Specifications: 
SetStatusBar changes the text which is currently displayed in the editor's
@{" status area " link "The TurboText Document Window"}.

The TEMPORARY option determines how long the new text is displayed in the
status area before it is replaced by the normal text. When TEMPORARY is
specified, the text is only displayed once, the next time the status area
is redrawn, the normal text is displayed. If the TEMPORARY option is not
specified, then the text remains in the status area for at least 5
seconds. The TEMPORARY option is useful when an operation is expected to
take a long time. You can set the status area to indicate that work in is
progress, and as soon as the operation is complete, and the status area is
redrawn, the normal text is redisplayed.

Passing no text to this command reverts to the normal status display.

See Also: @{" ActivateWindow " link "ActivateWindow"}
	  @{" BeepScreen     " link "BeepScreen"}
	  @{" GetErrorInfo   " link "GetErrorInfo"}
	  @{" Screen2Front   " link "Screen2Front"}
	  @{" Window2Front   " link "Window2Front"}

@endnode


@node "ShiftLeft"

Format:		ShiftLeft [number of characters] [TABS]

Template:	COUNT/N,TABS/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Shift the current line or currently selected block towards the left.

Specifications: 
ShiftLeft shifts the current line or currently @{" selected block " link "Selection Blocks"} a single
character to the left. This is done by deleting spaces or tabs at the start
of lines. All tab characters within the lines are also converted to spaces
before shifting.

If there is currently a selected block, the operation is applied to this
block, otherwise the operation is applied to the current line only.

Starting with TurboText 2.0, the COUNT option lets you specify the number
of characters by which to shift the line. If COUNT is not specified, then
the line is shifted by one character.

Starting with TurboText 2.0, the TABS option lets you specify that text
should be shifted in tab-sized increments. The size of a tab character is
determined by the current preferences settings.

If a line doesn't have a sufficient number of characters to satisfy the
COUNT parameter, the line is shifted as much as possible, and no error is
generated.

See Also: @{" ShiftRight " link "ShiftRight"}

@endnode


@node "ShiftRight"

Format:		ShiftRight [number of characters] [TABS]

Template:	COUNT/N,TABS/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Shift the current line or currently selected block towards the right.

Specifications: 
ShiftRight shifts the current line or currently @{" selected block " link "Selection Blocks"} a single
character to the right. This is done by inserting spaces at the start of
lines. All tab characters within the lines are also converted to spaces
before shifting.

If there is currently a selected block, the operation is applied to this
block, otherwise the operation is applied to the current line only.

Starting with TurboText 2.0, the COUNT option lets you specify the number
of characters by which to shift the line. If COUNT is not specified, then
the line is shifted by one character.

Starting with TurboText 2.0, the TABS option lets you specify that text
should be shifted in tab-sized increments. The size of a tab character is
determined by the current preferences settings.

See Also: @{" ShiftLeft " link "ShiftLeft"}

@endnode


@node "ShowFold"

Format:		ShowFold [NESTED | ALL]

Template:	NESTED/S,ALL/S

Release:	Version 1.0

Purpose: 
Expand folds.

Specifications: 
ShowFold displays the contents of currently hidden @{" folds " link "Folds"}. Once
displayed, the fold can be remade using the HideFold command. Invoked by
itself, this command displays the fold currently under the cursor only.
When provided the NESTED option all folds within the current fold are also
displayed. When passed the ALL option, all folds within the current
document are displayed.

See Also: @{" HideFold   " link "HideFold"}
